Most founders think about growth in terms of sales calls, fundraising decks, or paid ads, but Anthony Pierri, co-founder of FletchPMM and a featured speaker at the Startup Mountain Summit, took a different approach. He built his product marketing agency to $1.3M in annual revenue almost entirely through authentic thought leadership on LinkedIn.

Anthony’s path to entrepreneurship wasn’t a straight line. He originally planned to become a high school English teacher. Life, however, led him to a master’s in theology and 11 years as a pastor, where he led services and managed teams of over 75 volunteers. That experience taught him how to build community, guide people, and clearly communicate complex ideas, skills that later become central to his work with startups.

Today, Anthony co-leads FletchPMM, a product marketing agency that has helped 400+ B2B software companies find their ideal positioning strategy and bring it to life on newly crafted homepages. Their mission is simple: fixing confusing positioning.

FletchPMM is laser-focused on helping SaaS startups clearly communicate their value and stand out in crowded markets.